Generate a new scene in valid JSON format:

```json
{
  "scene_name": "A short evocative name for the scene",
  "description": "A 2-3 sentence description of what the player sees and senses as they enter this new location. Set the mood and hint at potential interactions.",
  "situation_aspects": [
    "First situation aspect (environmental or social feature)",
    "Second situation aspect"
  ],
  "npcs": [
    {
      "name": "NPC Name (only if dramatically appropriate)",
      "high_concept": "Brief high concept",
      "disposition": "friendly|neutral|hostile"
    }
  ]
}
```

Rules:
- scene_name should be 2-5 words
- description should be immersive and set the tone
- situation_aspects should be 2-3 invokable/compellable aspects
- npcs array can be empty if no NPCs are present; include at most 1-2 NPCs
- Keep the scene open-ended to allow player agency
{{- if .Scenario}}
- Create scenes that advance toward answering the story questions
- Include elements that relate to the scenario's central problem
{{- end}}
{{- if .PreviousSummaries}}
- Reference or build upon unresolved threads from previous scenes when appropriate
- NPCs encountered previously may reappear or be referenced
{{- end}}
